column5: Used to go over that going to the old Naughty Pines in the 90's and Andersons Manitou Falls remote cabin one time. That is by far more water than I ever saw flowing through there! Later, Jay
Stayed at Anderson's outpost down the river 3 times,now that place was a piece of work,the guy really did himself in.
This is the Wabigoon river on hwy 609 in Quibell.Not the falls on hwy 105 .same water though.

Yep, I didn't remember the railroad bridge being there. The one I was thinking it was is on 804 west of Ear Falls. I remember it as being Bailey bridge and the same type bridge. Very very similar. Later, Jay
Yes I have seen that one and been over it a few times.
